### What are Reactive Forms?

Reactive forms are model-driven — the form structure is defined in the component class using TypeScript. They provide more control, better testability, and easier validation compared to template-driven forms.

### Setup

```typescript
import { ReactiveFormsModule } from '@angular/forms';

@NgModule({
  imports: [ReactiveFormsModule]
})
export class AppModule { }
```

### FormControl and FormGroup

**FormControl** — Tracks the value and validity of a single input.
**FormGroup** — Groups multiple FormControls together.

```typescript
import { FormControl, FormGroup, Validators } from '@angular/forms';

@Component({...})
export class LoginComponent {
  loginForm = new FormGroup({
    email: new FormControl('', [Validators.required, Validators.email]),
    password: new FormControl('', [Validators.required, Validators.minLength(6)])
  });

  onSubmit() {
    if (this.loginForm.valid) {
      console.log(this.loginForm.value);
    }
  }
}
```

### Template Binding

```html
<form [formGroup]="loginForm" (ngSubmit)="onSubmit()">
  <input formControlName="email" type="email" />
  <input formControlName="password" type="password" />
  <button type="submit" [disabled]="loginForm.invalid">Login</button>
</form>
```

- **`[formGroup]`** — Binds the FormGroup to the form element.
- **`formControlName`** — Binds a FormControl within the group.

### FormBuilder

`FormBuilder` is a service that provides syntactic sugar for creating forms:

```typescript
constructor(private fb: FormBuilder) {
  this.loginForm = this.fb.group({
    email: ['', [Validators.required, Validators.email]],
    password: ['', [Validators.required, Validators.minLength(6)]]
  });
}
```

The array syntax is: `[initialValue, validators, asyncValidators]`.

### FormArray

For dynamic lists of controls:

```typescript
@Component({...})
export class OrderComponent {
  orderForm = this.fb.group({
    items: this.fb.array([
      this.fb.group({ product: '', quantity: 1 })
    ])
  });

  get items() {
    return this.orderForm.get('items') as FormArray;
  }

  addItem() {
    this.items.push(this.fb.group({ product: '', quantity: 1 }));
  }
}
```

### Observing Changes

```typescript
ngOnInit() {
  this.loginForm.valueChanges.subscribe(val => console.log(val));
  this.loginForm.statusChanges.subscribe(status => console.log(status));

  // Individual control
  this.loginForm.get('email')?.valueChanges.subscribe(val => console.log(val));
}
```

### Nested FormGroups

```typescript
profileForm = this.fb.group({
  name: [''],
  address: this.fb.group({
    street: [''],
    city: [''],
    zip: ['']
  })
});
```
```html
<div formGroupName="address">
  <input formControlName="street" />
  <input formControlName="city" />
  <input formControlName="zip" />
</div>
```

codeExample:
constructor(private fb: FormBuilder) {
  this.userForm = this.fb.group({
    name: ['', Validators.required],
    email: ['', [Validators.required, Validators.email]],
    address: this.fb.group({
      street: [''],
      city: [''],
      zip: ['']
    })
  });
}

